- Disabling public network access
- Restricting access to azure services without also specifying a subnet to restrict too.

issue.title: Network Security Rules fail to deploy due to too much priority
issue.body:
NSG has security rules and each rule increases the priority by 100.
The max value before ARM fails is 4100 so basically due to Farmer, there is artificial limitation of 41 rules.

You run out of line-numbers if you increment by 100, but if you increment by one, then you cannot easily modify your existing construct. Like in a very old BASIC language!

There are multiple possible solutions:
- Increase less, e.g. per 5 only!
- Custom priority field in securityRule
- Or a priority-incrementor setting in NSG

issue.title: Network Security Rules fail to deploy due to too much priority
issue.body:
NSG has security rules and each rule increases the priority by 100.
The max value before ARM fails is 4100 so basically due to Farmer, there is artificial limitation of 41 rules.

You run out of line-numbers if you increment by 100, but if you increment by one, then you cannot easily modify your existing construct. Like in a very old BASIC language!

There are multiple possible solutions:
- Increase less, e.g. per 5 only!
- Custom priority field in securityRule
- Or a priority-incrementor setting in NSG
